CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 5, 1958, pg. B1, reads: "Interesting Score - Anthony Strilko's composition for piano and cello is being studied by personnel of the Music Division of Carnegie Library. Shown above are Richard Osiier, pianist; Miss Irene Millen, head of the Music Division of Carnegie Library of Pittsburgh, and James Lumberger, counter tenor.  The interesting composition was presented to the library last week. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pianist Richard Osiier, librarian Irene Millen, and tenor James Lumberger holding musical score in music department, Carnegie Library of Pittsburgh
